    <main id="recipe-container">

        <!-- Main Heading -->
        <h1>The Ultimate Easy Fried Rice and Chicken</h1>

        <!-- Introductory Paragraph -->
        <p class="intro-paragraph">
            This classic, savory Fried Rice and Chicken recipe is a foundational dish in many households, known for its incredible flavor and versatility. It's a perfect weeknight meal that turns leftover rice into a vibrant, satisfying feast. The key to success is using **day-old rice** and cooking everything quickly over high heat to achieve that signature "wok hei," or smoky flavor.
        </p>

        <!-- Image relevant to the recipe -->
        <div class="recipe-image-container">
            <img 
                src="https://placehold.co/800x400/22c55e/ffffff?text=Delicious+Fried+Rice+and+Chicken" 
                alt="A plate of freshly made, steaming fried rice topped with sliced chicken and green onions." 
                class="recipe-image"
                onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='https://placehold.co/800x400/22c55e/ffffff?text=Fried+Rice+and+Chicken+Placeholder';"
            >
        </div>

        <!-- Ingredients Section -->
        <section class="ingredients-section">
            <h2>Ingredients & Materials Needed</h2>
            <!-- Unordered List of Ingredients -->
            <ul class="ingredient-list">
                <li>1.5 cups cooked white rice (ideally day-old)</li>
                <li>1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast or thighs, cubed</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Soy Sauce (plus extra for seasoning)</li>
                <li>1 tbsp Oyster Sauce (optional, but recommended)</li>
                <li>1 tsp Sesame Oil</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Vegetable Oil (for frying)</li>
                <li>2 cloves Garlic, minced</li>
                <li>1/2 cup diced Onion</li>
                <li>1/2 cup frozen Peas and Carrots mix</li>
                <li>2 large Eggs, lightly beaten</li>
                <li>Salt and White Pepper to taste</li>
                <li>A large Wok or large frying pan</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Instructions Section -->
        <section class="instructions-section">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <!-- Ordered List of Steps -->
            <ol class="instruction-steps">
                <li>
                    **Prepare the Chicken:** In a bowl, toss the cubed chicken with 1 tbsp Soy Sauce, Oyster Sauce, and a pinch of white pepper. Set aside for 5 minutes.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Cook the Chicken:** Heat 1 tbsp of oil in the wok over high heat. Add the chicken and stir-fry until fully cooked and lightly browned. Remove the chicken from the wok and set aside.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Scramble the Eggs:** Add a little more oil to the wok. Pour in the beaten eggs and quickly scramble them until set. Push the eggs to one side of the wok.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Saut√© Aromatics:** Add the remaining oil to the empty side of the wok. Add the minced garlic and diced onion, and stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Add the Rice:** Add the day-old rice to the wok. Use a spatula to break up any clumps. Stir-fry rapidly for 2-3 minutes to heat the rice and lightly toast the grains.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Incorporate Vegetables:** Add the frozen peas and carrots mix. Continue stir-frying until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Combine and Season:** Return the cooked chicken and scrambled eggs to the wok. Add the remaining 1 tbsp of Soy Sauce and the Sesame Oil. Stir everything together quickly to evenly coat the ingredients.
                </li>
                <li>
                    **Final Adjustment:** Taste the rice and add salt and white pepper as needed. Serve immediately while hot!
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>

    </main>

